Sappy has integrated Telegram/TON stickers into Sappy products as limited edition emotes and expressions.

This means Stickers/Gifts can be used as interoperable assets across real applications that will reach millions of players and users. These are not low effort Telegram minigames. They are high production value, fully fledged video game titles and platforms *made by us* that we will be integrating into.

More information is available in the tweet below on this first of its kind integration.

Sappy will be the #1 ecosystem on Telegram.

I don't like to get involve in this circus, but I will share my personal opinion about the situation üöΩ

**Why did Ton Foundation created NFT 2.0?
**TF started NFT 2.0 after they witnessed the success of my off-chain marketplace architecture üß†

They assumed the Telegram Gifts would be mintable from day 1 and everyone would use getgems(TF's favourite marketplace) and they would control the narrative. But Telegram added 21 days limit due to Stars refunds, so everyone started to deal OTC through guarantors or p2p and many users were scammed. And then [**Tonnel Marketplace**](https://t.me/TonnelGift/25) was created and you know the rest of story(Thank you again for your support since day 1 ‚ù§Ô∏è)

**What is NFT 2.0?**
In short, bullshit üöΩ

In more details, it's a [centralised system](https://docs.ton.org/v3/documentation/dapps/assets/nft-2.0) to ban your NFTs if you don't pay your sale tax(Big Brother is watching you) ü§° 

Don't be shocked, creators of this standard has no interest or respect to concept of freedom, privacy or autonomy. 

**Will Telegram support this standard? 
**NO(I'm 99.999% sure)üòí
If yes, I will probably uninstall my Telegram app and farm potatoesüåø

I sincerely ask you, if you have slightest dignity, please don't waste your hard-earned money in TF's traps, and do not buy or invest even 1 TON in TF's circus ü§ù
